// After creating this, in VS Code click the environment name in the bottom-right status bar 
// (or Ctrl+Shift+P → "Rest Client: Switch Environment") and pick dev — that's what makes {{baseUrl}} etc. resolve.
// baseurl or usertoken , admin token , categoryid , productid , ticketid , addressid in .vscode/settings.json

### Create Ticket (logged-in user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "subject": "Order not delivered",
  "message": "My order was placed 5 days ago and still shows pending status"
}

### Get My Tickets
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/my-tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Get All Tickets (admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Update Ticket Status (admin only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "resolved"
}